{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_019PqPtagQ4osE3ymuGVG3xE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_012ZTaHoLUN2nUwmrMgWVXjU","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/306-fee-accounting-audit/spec.md","old_string":"- [ ] [backend] In `backend/src/routes/referral.ts` `POST /claim`, replace `getPendingBalanceByUserId` with two ledger-derived checks via the new helpers: claim ≤ `getUserReferralAvailable(userId)` and claim ≤ `getReferralBucketAvailable()`. Keep the existing `referralMinClaimLamports` policy gate. Inside the same `sql.begin` transaction that inserts the `referral_claims` row and emits the queue event, also insert a `fee_bucket_debits` row (`bucket='referral'`, `debit_type='claim'`, `source_id=claim.id`, `status='pending'`). Confirm the existing `insertReferralEarning` / `getPendingBalanceByUserId` are still used elsewhere, or delete them with grep evidence.","new_string":"- [x] [backend] In `backend/src/routes/referral.ts` `POST /claim`, replace `getPendingBalanceByUserId` with two ledger-derived checks via the new helpers: claim ≤ `getUserReferralAvailable(userId)` and claim ≤ `getReferralBucketAvailable()`. Keep the existing `referralMinClaimLamports` policy gate. Inside the same `sql.begin` transaction that inserts the `referral_claims` row and emits the queue event, also insert a `fee_bucket_debits` row (`bucket='referral'`, `debit_type='claim'`, `source_id=claim.id`, `status='pending'`). Confirm the existing `insertReferralEarning` / `getPendingBalanceByUserId` are still used elsewhere, or delete them with grep evidence. (done: iteration 10)"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":472,"cache_read_input_tokens":143540,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":472},"output_tokens":2,"service_tie